# BIDEN DENOUNCES CAMPUS VIOLENCE, BREAKING SILENCE

BACKS LAWFUL DISSENT

President Rejects ‘Chaos’ Over War in Gaza as Arrests Increase

# BY PETER BAKER

WASHINGTON — President Biden broke off a dinner on Thursday to finally speak out on the wave of protests in American college campuses against Israel's war in Gaza that have sullamed much of the country, denouncing violence and antisemitism even as he defended the right to peaceful dissent.
